Major rice insect pests include: the brown planthopper (BPH),[159] several species of stemborersâ€”including those in the genera Scirpophaga and Chilo,[160] the rice gall midge,[161] several species of rice bugs,[162] notably in the genus Leptocorisa,[163] defoliators such as the rice: leafroller, hispa and grasshoppers.[164] The fall army worm, a species of Lepidoptera, also targets and causes damage to rice crops.[165] Rice weevils attack stored produce.
